content: Masterpiece, this game makes you think. While it might be a point and click with done dragging, try it and see how long it takes you. Such an interesting perspective, but keeps you on your toes and your brain freshly thinking. This is my favorite game on the app store.
This game does not work, only goes to white screen of death.
One of the best games I've ever played, so imaginative and just the right amount of challenging. Can't believe how good it is.
One of the most mesmerizing gaming experiences I have ever played. Beautiful artwork, clever puzzling. A must play mobile game that's so satisfying to finish.
the most difficult game ever

Incredibly annoying. No instructions and the demo doesn't play, so I just kept having to randomly click on things until something that made little sense happened. Then random clicking until some other random thing happened and so on. To the game designers: provide some instructions so that the game makes sense!
Loved it! Very challenging and I loved that!
This game is stunning! Absolutely brilliant. So many clever solutions to the puzzles, and so many "AHA" moments when finding those solutions. One of the best games I've ever played!
Boring.
Beautiful and frustrating. I thoroughly enjoyed it!
Very surreal and beautiful! üòç
Imagine walking through a haiku that requires you to use your puzzle solving skills to get to the next line. That's what this game is like.
It's unbelievably beautiful. I've played through it twice already.
Wonderfully new and refreshing. Just hard enough to be interesting without a frustrating learning curve.
Wow. Gorgeous and challenging.
Amazingly beautiful game, didn't quite get the story but the puzzles were entertaining, unique and challenging.
So refreshingly different, unique and beautiful. I'm hoping for a second chapter!
This is an absolutely amazing game. The art work is incredible. Best game I've ever played or seen.

Paid and downloaded this app, it has Zero instructions and zero hints. The farawy series costs yes but they have a hint system in place and their games dont end in an hour and a half. Criminal investigation costs zero and I have been playing for a couple of years. This game can be played off line but that really does not count since I have to run to YouTube every 2 min. for my next move. YOUR GAME SUCKS. Oh and I uninstalled - I needed the space, decided to reinstall ,now it won't..?refund!
Would not work. I tried demo mode and was left with a blank screen no matter what I did. Not happy.
Won't run on my Pixel 4a 5g
Stunningly clever puzzle game. A unique and complexly designed piece. Beautiful art, and rich music and sound effects. A story that feels both grounded and mythological. Great experience.
Best puzzle game! So unique
Great game play! Very few instructions, but not too hard to figure out. I was stuck on the tram for a while and the blue thingy was also challenging. Would play any follow up games!
Amazing. A piece of art.
Short but weird and lovely, also creepy.
Just beautiful and intriguing. Please be patient and stick with it. Or try a walkthrough video just to get past a stuck part. Loved it!
Het spel opent niet, ik krijg een wit scherm
New twist on a puzzle game with brilliant graphics and intriguing puzzles...left me wanting more.
no puzzles, may i have my money back?

Sent 2 emails to devs and never got a response. Game doesn't load, gets stuck on all white screen. Worked briefly and then after uninstalling and reinstalling all I get is the white screen... Restarted phone, cleared cache, tried internal and external storsge, deleted and reinstalled... Nothing works. I want a refund or a fix... Small dev right? I should hace a response.

What a unique and creative game. I loved how it was mysterious and the right difficulty level for casual playing. I wanted something I could easily pick up and put down and this hit the mark. The artwork and story are beautiful. I think I will play through again to truly enjoy all the little details I may have missed. There were no ads, no push notifications - making this a peaceful retreat. Thank you!
This is the most beautiful game. I wish there were more like it.
I really enjoyed this game. Nice graphics. Very unique in its design, by having to zoom on items, overlap and adjust windows. It could have been nicer if it was a little longer.
Not working on Android, no response from customer service - happy to delete this review if I ever hear back as I heard that this game is supposed to be amazing.
Great!
Desperately needs a dark theme for visual impaired. The white background overwhelmes the pictures. Unplayable for me. Print needs to be bigger. Note 8 ultimate.
Incredible. Best I have played yet. Very original puzzle ideas, the soundtrack and art are brilliant
I got stuck and despite checking the walkthrough I'm still stuck, tried for days and eventually gave up. Beautiful game and I was really enjoying it. I play a lot of games but this is frustrating.
This game was very challenging and hard at sometimes but l really enjoyed the game and hope the developers come out with another game like this l would buy it. The game is great.
beautiful!
Pretty kool concept. Waiting for part two. Or possibly more of these puzzles.
Enchanting and imaginative

A beautifully rendered journey through space and time with inventive puzzle mechanics. Tells an emotional story wonderfully without any text or dialogue. My only complaint is that I wish there was more! More than worth the money.

This game is genius. As far as point and click-style adventure puzzle games go, this is visually lovely with a quality storyline and some of the most unique, clever gameplay I've ever experienced. I'm shocked more people haven't played it. The only thing that bums me out, is that it's a tiny bit on the short side. Regardless, it is well worth a play, and even worth a replay. I couldn't recommend this more.
What a unique, awesome puzzle game. More please Jason.

Not a puzzle so much as a random point and click and drag guessing game. I wish there were something to solve, or something to think through. Instead it's just a bunch of tiles you click and drag and sometimes you click or drag into the right place or have waited through the right animation and click again and the result is different. No puzzles here, just random, but pretty, art trying to be a game.
Couldn't play while lying down because of auto rotate. :(
Love this game! My only complaint is that it was too short!
Beauty
Beautifully designed, with a thoughtful plot and inventive puzzles.

This is probably good for experienced gamers but I am not an experienced gamer and I can't figure out what the puzzle is or what you're supposed to do. I played for about 10 minutes and I just keep seeing these extremely tiny pictures that don't do anything. It would be nice if there were instructions or comments or something.

Beautiful game, I did not really understand the story behind it but it kept me hooked for a few hours while I played. Which is really impressive for me. Totally worth the money. Just wish it was a bit longer or I could play another game like it. I loved the moving the tiles to make a new picture, I have never seen a game like it! Really, really enjoyed this.
Too small! I can't see it on my Samsung a50. It's the size of a postage stamp!
Loved this game. Beautiful graphics and great puzzles. Like others, would definitely recommend not using walk-throughs.
Great game, interesting, fascinating concept. Too short, not with 5$. Id pay 2$ but honestly I just wish it was longer, because it is a good game.
Brilliant concept, beautiful artwork and gameplay that was challenging but not frustrating. Hope there's a sequel.
Superb, brain twisting adventure puzzle with gorgeous graphics and soundtrack. My only complaint is that it was way too short, but still worth the few euros I paid for it.
Awesome puzzle game
wow! Beautiful, creative and contemplative.
Amazing game. A bit confusing at first as there really isn't any direction. Once you figure out gameplay it's truly fantastic and requires brain cells to be on!
A must play masterpiece. Not very long, but intense. A true example of art in video games.
A wonderful, enchanting experience. I didn't want it to end.
Very unique game with amazing graphics, but way too short for $4.99 I finished the game in less than 2 hours
Best mobile game i have ever played
Outstanding app. Beautifully drawn with a unique approach to setting and solving puzzles. Well done I say!
One of the best puzzle games I've played. I can't wait for another one

Poorly thought out design. I usually love puzzle games. Its my thing. This is a load of random guess work. I'm sure there's a plenty of people patting themselves on the back for guessing their way through this collection of misbegotten mess, thinking themselves clever. It's essentially a glorified Pachinko machine. There's no consistent logic to the puzzles. It's so random the game has to continually prompt you. How do I organise a refund?
Installed twice. Try to play demo and it freezes, nothing happens. Sad waste of money.

This game is wonderful. Very out of the box type game play. I originally saw it on my ps4 store.. was a bit expensive but then I saw it here cheaper.. so worth the money!! Not an easy game but that's what I was looking for!!
Beautiful game, so cool when things line up.
Wanted to enjoy this, but just kept getting stuck at the same point with no way to go beyond. Feel ripped off.
Just beautiful
Brilliantly creative game, got me frustrated at certain points but once I realised the mechanics of it, it was so enjoyable

This was amazing. it is a truly unique puzzle solving experience. I loved it and really hope the developers do others like this. The game is short... but I really think it's worth the money. I'm going to go through it again to be able to experience all the graphics.
Beautiful artwork. Got through the first 2 levels but keep getting stuck on the third, with only tiles I can do nothing with. But I will keep trying, now and again...
Fantastic. There are other games that follow the same concept (ex. FRAMED), but this one takes the cake for being so inventive and tell a story as complex as the puzzles!

What a charming and challenging game. The puzzles are tricky, but the game follows a logic and builds a syntax of storytelling that reinforces itself. As others have said, don't use walkthroughs if you can help it. The will give you two hints: the positioning of the panes often matters, and there are dynamic puzzles with multiple layers. Enjoy.
It won't load for me and I don't know how to get a refund. Grrr
This game comes with no directions. The demo didn't work. It was a waste of $4.99
Challenging and beautiful. It has no instructions or explanation, you just jump right in by tapping and moving. You have to go along with the subtle hints and experiment.
Mind-blowing !
A beautiful experience. Well worth the price
beautifully made and challanging my favorite game when is the next one?
Inspiring artwork and unique games concept. Not difficult to solve the puzzles but the whole experience is powerful. Loved it!
Really enjoyable, I now want more by this designer
Great game but a little glitchy

This is an amazing game with incredible and unusual mechanics. The puzzles progressed in a great way, lots of interesting challenges. However, nearly all of the people in this game are depressed, despairing, dirty, etc. And for no reason. It could have great replay value, but I found it too heavy in spirit, so I won't play again.
That was the most satisfying puzzle game I have ever played. The mood, the graphics, the puzzles themselves all combined to create a wonderful fantasy mystery mood. Highly recommend.
Innovative, intriguing and challenging. Beautiful storyboards. Would like to see more games like this.
Great engaging game but would have preferred more rounds/episodes.
Good to waste an afternoon. Won't hold interest beyond that.

This is fun, beautiful, and thought provoking. The gameplay is unique, no words and simple controls where every moment is enjoyable to watch, and every discovery is an a-ha moment of fun. I hope more games that are this innovative are released. But if not, this gem exists.
A cure for conformity
Excellent game, so creative and original. To be honest I've not played anything quite like it.
Finished in about 2.5hrs but was an intriguing, mind bending puzzle. Lateral thinking needed!
Beautiful, unique. I would like more of this, and using these mechanics, please.
I thought it was a challenging fun game! Hopefully there's a part 2.

Really fun A little expensive for a game that is done in a few hours. BUT it is so different than anything I've ever played, I don't regret it. It takes some different thinking and a lot of figuring things out on your own, but it's very rewarding to start to gradually uncover the clues and slowly put the pieces together to solve everything. Overall a great game I would very much recommend.
Unable to play the game. Choosing the demo froze the app. After clearing cache and storage the app would not then open. Requesting refund
Totally unique game! There are no instructions or directions, but THAT IS THE GAME! To figure out how to play or move ahead! If you like "this causes that" type thinking, then get this!

It's visually appealing and a good puzzle game. I killed 2.5 hours until i finished it so the $5 was okay, I guess. I don't anticipate ever playing it again though so I would have preferred more levels.

Shorter than I expected, providing about 5 hours of gaming total. However, I had to really think out of the box, a totally unique experience. It was absorbing and engaging. No words, purely visual puzzles, graphics were good. Very loose story could be interpreted from the series of images presented in the game. Offline, solo experience.
Beautiful graphics, love the story and the way it was told. Frustrated by not knowing what to do in a few parts, but the satisfaction of getting it on my own was so worth it. Overall I loved it!

Wow next level !! Took me a while to get into, as it has very unique gameplay, but what a ride. Recommend playing this alongside someone else as you need two brains to solve this one. Only criticism is the demo doesn't work - screen goes white and stops - tried on two different phone, otherwise perfect. Well done to the developers for this beautiful work of art and excellent game.

I'm not an avid gamer,but this was very special. Once you go down the rabbit whole the mystery of the game goes deeper and deeper. Absolutely beautiful, artistic experience. Really got the brain working Loved it.
Beautiful game, loved it!
Interesting premise, interesting game play, evocative storyline
Mind bending puzzles, minimal frustration. Beautifully illustrated and executed. A classic
Loved the game, it's beautiful and intriguing, would be 5 star if a bit longer. I think it will have a special appeal to artists.
beautiful game! I need some more levels tho, I beat it in an evening... unless I'm maybe missing something?
Beautiful game. Challenging but not frustrating. Really enjoy playing!
Excellent game, really wonderful drawing and style, super creative puzzles. Story itself is engaging and clever. Just perfect.
Beautiful and challenging. I've played it a few times. Each time I see something new. I want to know more about the boy/man now. How did he fall from the tower?
Absolutely gorgeous, but also very engaging game play. The story is well written, and even includes a few last moment surprises!
The demo in the game doesn't work. Nothing big a blank screen and the only way to get out of it is to close the app. Would love to see the demo so I have an idea of what I'm supposed to do.....
it's hard. works the brain so if you have a fun carefree time find differmy game

Great but too short. Its a beautiful and intriguing game, mechanics are taught slowly but strongly. Wish some puzzles were longer and could exploit some mechanics a bit longer. Some story in it would be nice too. Could be a perfect game but I really found it too short.
Stunning and beautiful, I wish this game was longer!

It being the first time I've paid for a game in a long time, I have to say that I was very disappointed on my purchase. The game itself has beautiful graphics but with no rules, guidelines or hints that explain what you are actually suppose to do, sadly made this game more puzzling than an actual puzzle
This game is so beautiful, and imo, the perfect length. Gorgeous.
I didn't want it to end!

Beautiful, atmospheric graphics. Very nice puzzle.

Every now and then I find an game that blows me away and that I particularly enjoy - Aquaria, Braid, Monument Valley, and this. Hats off to the designer for this excellent and mind-bending work. I would also like to add that if I ever see a giant rainbow monster weaving through the buildings in the distance outside my window, my first thought will not be to look it up and figure out how to meet it.
A game unlike any other. Try it to know it.
Unique. One of a kind!

A really stunning game. It didn't initially work on my (quite old) tablet but I re-installed onto my phone (at no extra cost, thank you Google Play!) and it works perfectly. I can't recommend Gorogoa highly enough. Gorgeous artwork, and puzzles that are challenging but not impossible. It's not a long game, but I will be playing it more than once to fully appreciate all the beautiful subtleties. Very glad I purchased it, worth every penny.
On Nokia 8 the game does not start. Only a white background with GOROGOA title screen, and remain frozen. Please fix it.
Simple yet very challenging. unique but vaguely familiar. entraping.
Something is going wrong almost straight away. I checked YouTube and I'm not getting all the images. Annoying as I never pay for games and thought I'd treat myself. Prob just need to delete. Thanks
Beautiful, intriguing game!
An amazing experience and easily one of my favourite game in all platforms. I have played this game almost 10 times and I still am not yet tired of it. I even bought the game for a few of my friends.
I've played through this game twice now with a couple months between, still captivating. I really like the lack of directions and speaking. Gotta really figure it out yourself.
Exceptional game.
Great game!
Unique and Amazing! I was immediately hooked and have played through multiple times already. The story is done very well. I want more!

Short but delightful. If you liked monument valley this might be for you. Seriously filled me with joy. Puzzles are brain teasers but not annoyingly hard. (You can turn off hints before you start! Found out after I finished...)
Challenging in a good way. It's a keeper. Like playing it again to see what I remember.
Beautiful. Really different from others of its kind.
Beautiful game
An incredible, at your own pace, well thought through game. It's a unique type of puzzle that I really enjoyed.
It was beautifully imagined, set, and scored. I highly recommend it. Looking forward to others things the author may have done.
Beautiful and inventive.
Awesome concept

Fantastic game to settle down with and forget everything else going on around you. There were multiple times where this game's novel concept surprised me. The ending was bittersweet, as I wanted to keep playing more! There's just enough story to keep you wondering. Highly recommend!
It should teach you a little play tutorial as the game was so different and original that it got confusing to me straight away on what to do...great job though

Unique and creative. Challenging at times. Beautifully done. I truly loved the story and gameplay. I have never played a game like this before and thoroughly enjoyed it. It felt short, only because it was so engaging and I wanted it to keep going!

This is utterly beautiful. I'm not usually particularly interested in gaming apps, but this is more of a work of art which you can wander around, with a very pleasing symmetry to the puzzles. Highly recommended on all levels.
Beautiful, unique, and challenging. This game is a precious work of art.

Great game! Clever gameplay concept. I did feel It's a shame there are no pinch to zoom or swioe to pan, but I'm sure there's a good reason for that. I'd recommend playing on a tablet for better view of things. Recommended!
Brilliant game! Had me hooked. Even when I thought I was stuck, looking at things a different way gave me the solution. I smiled the whole way through. Loved it

My Lord! This is a Fantastic Game!

Not like any puzzle game I have ever played. Had me hooked from start to finish. Every penny worth it.
Well designed, but very short.
Beautiful game
Very challenging and fun!

Beautiful design, but gets confusing to the point of being annoying and boring. I was enjoying it, but even just the chapter menu is like a puzzle. Got to the point I was just going round in circles, endlessly tapping things until something random happened, so I gave up.
Perfection.
So smart, fun, and moving... Great game.

What a unique, engaging approach to gameplay mechanics! Also, the story has kept me wondering, even after finishing it. I've replayed it a few times to really appreciate the artwork and animations (double-tap a panel to enlarge it) and to revisit the story. This game was clearly the result of much love, and easily worth the asking price. I'm a bit sad I can't discover it from scratch all over again. I wish it was longer. What beautiful escapism! I look forward to this developer's next project.
Great and very original game
Very unique.
Crashes on one of the puzzles and the developers don't seem to concerned about fixing it.
Worth every penny. It's challenging but not impossible. The story and illustrations are on a different level.
One of the best games I have ever played at. I would really recommend it. Only, it is not immediate at the beginning, don't be discouraged
Masterpiece

I'm sure this game deserves every one of its positive reviews, but unfortunately I can't say the same. Not because the game is bad, but because it just won't start. Whenever I start the game, it just hangs on the title screen, and from other places on the net, it seems like this is a pretty common problem. So while I'd like to enjoy the game and leave a positive review, I can't since it seems there's no way for me to actually play the game.
Best puzzle game I've played
Excellent puzzle game, and beautifully done. Highly recommended.
What an original and unique puzzle game. I loved every second of it and only wish that it was longer. Please create more art like this.
Beautiful, original puzzler that I found very calming, just what is needed in this dystopian reality we are in now.

The art is GORGEOUS and the game flow is relatively smooth. Maybe for future games consider changing the zoom from double click to a drag and drop? It's easy to accidentally toggle out of zoom, and the 4x4 layout is too small to see all the amazing detail on mobile. Also, making animated panels bigger until the animation is over would highlight the beautiful design. Overall worth the $ just for the artwork imo
Beautiful and challenging.
Havent even played it yet but for me this is a must have i can just see how beautiful and clever it is i havent purchase from play store in a long time but i had to get this
The game is lovely... although, it will not let me go to the green candle anymore with the man lighting candles in Chapter 4. The highlight option somehow disappeared. So, now I am stuck.
Amazing game, a lot of fun. Didn't want it to end! Thank you
Nil experience as it will not install. I have downloaded it several times but no joy...which sucks. Can you please return my money.
Very special, very meditative. Very ground breaking puzzle presentation. Delightful, would absolutely recommend.
Amazing! Beautiful journey! Thank You! Thank You! Thank You!
Crashes on all devices tried
Beautiful and intriguing, just wish it was longer, I finished in less than 2 hrs
Gameplay was challenging and the art was fantastic!
A very fun and interesting little puzzle game. Do recommend
Very interesting game! It was a great experience! Different kind of puzzle... I loved it!
Incredibly innovative and fun to solve!
Omg!!!!... love

Absolutely amazing. One of the best games I've ever played. The art is so beautiful and the story really sucks you in. It's a dark lore adventure and each time you move a tile or combine images together, you get more and more surprised. Played it for a good 5 hours. I highly suggest you take your time as I am now regretting not being able to look forward to playing this anymore. I wish there were more games like this.
Amazing.

Beautiful game, awesome score, amazing atmosphere. The format allows for really creative mechanics, but most of them we only see briefly because there are some many ingenious ideas one after the other. My only complaints are minor; the plot is kind of hard to follow and there are a lot of characters to keep track of. It feels more like a first act then a completed game (especially for 5$). It ends when I thought the story was just taking shape.
Great game, really clever and innovative, I will be keeping my eyes open for the next one
Brilliant
Stunning graphics, good music, lovely story

Such an beautiful and sensation art! This game touched my deeply think about life in indescribable way. Brilliant! I love both of your game, Gorogoa and Florence. Hope to see another product from your studio!

Most original and imaginative gameplay I've seen. I was ooing and ahhing with every new discovery.... I played on a tablet so I'm not sure how it would look on a smaller scale screen.....the zoom function would help.... designing brilliance.
Absolutely beautiful game, intriguing storyline and challenging puzzles at time that force you to think differently. I just wish every puzzle game was as good as this.

After purchasing this app I realize I just don't get it?? No direction no help and just can not advance past the first 3 pictures. I really don't know how people are playing and loving it. Wish I could figure it out as I love a good challenge but after an hour my husband and I have given up. So refund please OR explain the concept please UPDATING MY REVIEW ; I TAKE AWAY MY ONE STAR BECAUSE EVERY ONE IS 5*s.PLUS 3 WORDS USED WAY TOO OFTEN BEAUTIFUL,GORGEOUS AND LOVELY CAUSE SAME PERSON WROTE ALL
Such an enjoyable puzzle game, so inventive! The story telling is beautiful, and the illustrations are exquisite. Unlike anything else, and worth the cost of the app.

Gorogoa is, for me, one of THE stand-out mobile games of the decade, right up there with Monument Valley and The Room. I can't think of another game that had me using lateral thinking as much as this one. The driving visual narrative, deep musical textures, and intimate graphics give this game a unique personality that left me craving more. In short: if you're still reading this, PLAY Gorogoa. The only regret you'll have is that there isn't a sequel yet.
Absolutely stunning graphics. Recommended
It's true it is a great unique game and I am a fan of The Room and Machinarium. My only thing is for the price, I'd wish it ran a little longer!!!
amazing experience. play with headphones!
Relatively short but wonderful game. I highly recommend. Clever game play and beautiful graphics.
Good game, but it ignores the screen rotation lock, which makes it completely unplayable when lying in bed.
Amazing game!

This game is marvelous. Such a wonderful and manageably challenging journey through different dimensions. I love how brilliantly the creators create movement elements and stunningly beautiful mosaics. A challenging artistic experience that is such a pleasure when beautiful adventure puzzles seem so few and far between. Absolutely delightful. I hope you have more for us very soon. Excellent work. I'm deeply grateful.
An enchanting morning's entertainment for ¬£3.50. Pretty fair price.
Exceptional game and innovate. Simple yet detailed graphics with a storyline that requires thinking to progress. Definitely not the usual point and click, I loved it.

Worth every penny! Incredible! Maybe the most interesting and surprising and innovative puzzle game I have ever played! Just enough hints to not be super frustrating, but hard enough that you will not breeze through it without having to pause and think, and think some more. Music is fitting, surprisingly not annoying, changes in sound effects for things happening are brilliant! Already telling others to play! WOW! Love it! Great job devs!
Totally absorbing. Visually stunning. It throws you into a different way of thinking
Short, but beautiful and fun.
I not working it keep freezing the Android I would like a refund please..
Spectacularly good.
WOW
Wheels within wheels. Never experienced a game like it. Great story, graphics and UI. More more!

Short game... hard to give a high rating when the story is completely obscure and the story / characterisation is pretty depressing. Also... What story? What is actually going on here? No idea. No idea what this is... Over far too quickly... Left feeling unsatisfied and actually want my money back. But cant. So hey ho. The game is about finding 5 differently-coloured balls. Then it ends. Actually sucks as an experience, quite repetitive.
Probably one of my favourite ever games. So clever and creative, nothing else quite like it.
Lovely game. I originally bought and played it on my PC through Steam. More than happy to pay to have it on my phone too.
Good game for an hour. Too short for $6.49
My favorite puzzle game. Complex and fluid; tough but so pleasant... and so dang gorgeous. Nice work!

This game is utterly amazing. I have never experienced anything quite like it before. One of the best value for my money ever. In order to fully immerse yourself in the puzzles, I strongly recommend turning off the hints. I encourage anyone who appreciates good puzzles and beautiful aesthetics to play this game.
Nice graphics, puzzles are reasonably difficult with nice hints in game.
Does not work on the Note 10+
Bravo! A beautiful, imaginative, and innovative game. I'm most impressed.

Downloaded on Pixel 2XL, but too small for my eyes. Tried to open on tablet but it wanted me to purchase again. So refunded on Pixel, then purchased on tablet. App won't open (black screen). Tablet is Nexus 9. Couldn't find any info on device compatibility. Refunded on tablet. This looks like a great game but can't say for sure since I can't play it :(
Amazing innovative puzzle game, it is rather short but worth it
Played on steam, bought it and played again on Android. TheThe art and puzzle design are awesome and stunning. The only downside is the short gameplay.
Great game, but way way WAY too short. Feel a bit ripped off.
The most beautiful game I've played on Android and possibly in any format. Exquisite and flawless.
It was challenging without being impossible. The puzzles are very unique. The only thing I would change is making it a little longer. It didn't take very long to finish.

This is a lovely relaxing game to play. It's not tremendously long, but the gameplay is straightforward to understand, even if it's tricky to solve the puzzles. There is one bit in the middle where there is a leap in understanding how the world works, which confused me, but apart from that it was enough of a puzzler to get a couple of hours from it. The game is beautiful, the hand drawn pictures throughout are lovely.
Most original puzzle game in years.

Such a beautiful game, fun game. I started it a while go, got stuck and put it down for a while. I came back to it played again from the beginning and really enjoyed it. You move a boy through different environments which you manipulate by shifting tiles of images to help him progress. My description barely does it justice, and I can't recommend it enough.
One of the most beautiful, original and interesting games I've ever experienced. Never quite seen anything like it. So cool! Well worth the purchase price. Hope you make more games Jason!

I would give this game 10 stars if I could!!! It is the most original and unique game I've ever played. The artwork is beautiful to boot! It is challenging and makes you think in ways other games don't. Definitely not your average video game! You will love it.
Simply superb, original navigation, beautiful narrative reveal.
Amazing! Beautiful and dark and smart
Stunning
Just amazing!
amazing game even though short story i enjoyed and worth the price
Beautiful, but I have NO idea what to do. There are no instructions at all. I guess it's supposed to be intuitive, but I'm completely lost.
Utterly absorbing and delightfully infuriating!

Absolutely stunning. Calming, yet very addictive! Music, artwork, creative puzzles, darkness and light--all of it, just breathtaking. I almost wish it were longer, but the ending was satisfyingly complete and perfect as all the rest, and an encore might have diminished the whole. Thank you for this experience.

Lovely puzzle game. Different, clever mechanics. Something new for a change. Great graphics and atmosphere too. Only problem, story is quite short, so if you get stuck, try not to look online for a hint. Give it time, prolong the experience, and you'll figure it out.

Beautifully rendered, subtle but entirely playable perspective puzzle game. It's not immediately obvious what to do and no instructions. Once I'd realised that you could zoom in on certain frames, remove them from the scene, move to another scene, reinsert the frame and 'capture' that section to shift perspective(!) I was off. There are common pictural elements that hint at which scenes fit together. You can even line up scenes and walk from one to another. Challenging, unique and very enjoyable

A marvelous triumph of pure fantasy. As the player, you have four panes in which the (wordless) story needs to unfold. I'm glad a dropped a few dollars on this.

A beautiful illustrated puzzle. You move scenes around and go deeper into the details of certain images or move further out to broaden the scope of your view. By making the pictures interact in certain ways, you propel the main character forward and get more details and a broader scope on his life story. A really well executed, thoughtful, and enjoyable experience.
awesome new way of doing puzzle.
Beautiful, unique and clever game. Over way too soon.
takes some getting used to the interface and mechanics but then wow! Original and beautiful game.

I seem to be having a very different experience than the majority of the others here. There are no instructions. No clue as to what I'm supposed to do or why. It certainly looks appealing and has obviously been made to a high standard, but does not engage or entertain me. Unfortunately by the time I had given it a bit of a chance I'd lost the opportunity to get a refund.

This game is legitimately amazing. I've never played anything quite like it. Think about a slide puzzle where every single tile has a world living inside it. These tiles have worlds in them which connect to other parallel worlds which exist in other tiles. Trust me when i say that this is a must play game.

harder puzzle game with story.

I feel like calling this game a work of art does it a disservice, because it suggests nothing more than an impressive visual style. Don't get me wrong, the game looks beautiful, but it's the completely original gameplay mechanics which elevate Gorogoa to something truly exceptional. The narrative is intrinsically linked to the puzzles so by solving you're not completing a side challenge, the method by which you proceed helps you understand the underlying themes of the game. Total masterpiece.
It's really innovative, great puzzles that really make you think outside the box, and also has amazing art. However, I think the time spent on solving it was too short for the price paid.
This is a delightful game that uses logic (and thinking outside the box) to progress and follow the storyline. I can't wait for more from this developer.
awesome....love the puzzles and graphics

This is an amazing game. To say that it is Framed meets Monument Valley meets The Room doesn't do it justice, but does give a hint at the mechanics. The puzzles are simple to begin with, although the rules are not explained so the player has to learn by observation and experiment. As the challenges become more intricate, good visual and spatial awareness is required, also some talent for lateral thinking. This game just keep getting richer and more rewarding as you progress.

This is a pretty crafty puzzle game. The art is amazing and the way the puzzles are arranged are engaging. Do yourself a favor if you get stuck, DON'T LOOK UP HINTS. Every puzzle has a solution and sometimes its just about the way you look at it. That moment you figure it out, feels great! Also, get the mobile version. The Steam version is 3 times the cost for the same game. It took me about an hour to beat it so not worth $15 on Steam, but worth the price here.

Interesting mechanics and beautiful visuals make for an enjoyable hour. But $5 seems a bit much given the breadth of content out there that gives you a better return on investment. Still, purchased with Google Rewards credit, it was worth it. But maybe wait to see if it goes on sale. And I can't imagine paying $15 on PC or console. I didn't see any of the technical issues others are complaining about. And it's definitely not a random point and click. Requires some lateral thinking, but logical.
Cute and kinda of a short game. I haven't seen anything like it. Overall good puzzle game!

Stunning! The simple storyline is easy told without any words. The artwork evokes emotion and the mechanics of gameplay invite the user to explore the art to solve the puzzle. Great idea, innovative controls and narrative, but maybe a bit too short.
Top Short. I need more Gorogoa!!
One of my all time favorites! Beautiful, curious, clever, and like nothing else.

I first posted a beta version of this game several years ago on PC and loved the experience. Periodically, I went back to check if any progress had been made and was disappointed that none had. Imagine my excitement to see a completed version available as a mobile download! As for a review the game had a unique mechanic of sliding around the frames on the screen to open up new areas to explore and make the frames interact with eachother. The goal is to collect 5 objects found throughout. Enjoy!

This game is gorgeous. The mechanics are truly unique (as far as I know). 
It is more of an trial and error exploration than puzzle. It is equally 
interesting to watch as it is to play. The interface was clearly not 
designed for phone screens, but it worked out anyway! I think the biggest 
weakness is that it tries to be a puzzle game at the same time as it tries 
to be an exploration which means that there are parts that infuriate me 
because they didn't build on the language of previous interactions, and 
then there are parts that just felt like grind because I knew the solution 
already, I just needed to go through all other views and randomly stumble 
upon the one specific fitting screen to progress. All in all, the 
experience just blew my mind. I really want to see more fully functional 
mind bending psychedelic video games.

This game is absolutely beautiful and the gameplay is perfectly balanced to

story. I loved every minute of it.

This game is so small on the phone that I couldn't see anything. It's 
unplayable unless you use a tablet. It's also very very confusing. I have 
played many a puzzle game and this one has been hands down the most 
confusing...and not in a good way. The game gives very little affordance to 
the user and every action you take has unexpected results. Although some 
people may like this and even say it's the point of this game I find it to 
be more an exercise in click all the things until one of them works. The 
games controls don't feel very good or intuitive. The game also randomly 
will crash from time to time, and doesn't give you any indication on when 
it saves. I have lost so much progress because of that... On the bright 
side it is very pretty and if you are the type of person who just likes to 
click around and try a bunch of actions then you might enjoy this.
